Ad Text:
Honeysuckle Health

At Honeysuckle Health, we’re on a mission to help people lead healthier lives by connecting them with effective, affordable and personalised care. Through digital and telephonic health programs, data-driven insights and strong industry partnerships, we’re building a more connected and value-driven healthcare system for all Australians. We’re a wholly owned member of the nib Group and are merging with nib’s digital health company, Midnight Health, to form an integrated health services organisation offering a broad suite of health programs and services.

Located in either Brisbane or Newcastle

We are seeking a highly skilled and experienced Data Engineer to join our team. The ideal candidate will be responsible for designing, developing, and maintaining data systems and infrastructure. The Data Engineer will work closely with data scientists, analysts, and other stakeholders to ensure that data is properly collected, stored, and analyzed to support business objectives.

Responsibilities:

Work with a team of product managers, data scientists, data analysts and software engineers
Implement our data strategy by providing expert guidance in data and machine learning engineering.
Implement the technical strategy for data infrastructure and ML systems
Implement architecture and design of scalable data pipelines and ML platforms
Collaborate with cross-functional teams to identify and implement ML solutions
Follow best practices for code quality, testing, and deployment
Work to project timelines, resources, and deliverables
Ensure data quality, security, and compliance standards are met
Partner with product and business stakeholders to align technical solutions with business goals

Candidate Criteria:

Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Engineering, or related field
Experience in data engineering or machine learning engineering
Strong programming skills in Python, SQL, or similar languages
Experience with cloud data technologies (Snowflake, Databricks, AWS, etc.)
Experience in developing and deploying ML models
Experience with cloud platforms (AWS, GCP, or Azure)
Understanding of data architecture and ML system design
Excellent problem-solving and analytical skills
Strong communication and leadership abilities

Preferred Skills:

Experience with MLOps tools and practices
Knowledge of containerization and orchestration (Docker, Kubernetes)
Familiarity with deep learning frameworks (TensorFlow, PyTorch)
Understanding of DevOps practices and CI/CD pipelines
Experience with data governance and compliance requirements
Knowledge of distributed systems and microservices architecture
Familiarity with agile development methodologies

Why join us?

Play a key role in one of the most exciting healthtech businesses in Australia
Flexible hybrid working from our Newcastle HQ
Employee health insurance discounts, paid parental leave and educational assistance
Collaborative, purpose-driven team
Opportunities for career growth in a dynamic, fast-paced environment
Visit honeysucklehealth.com.au and midnight.health to learn more about what we do

All applications are strictly confidential. Applicants must have full rights to work in Australia.

Ready to build a Healthier Future? Apply now and be part of a team that’s changing lives every day. Submit your cover letter and CV and let’s make healthcare history together!

As far as recruiters go, our internal People & Culture team has this role covered, so we will not accept unsolicited agency resumes.

Senior AI Solutions Developer

Location: Sydney (Hybrid)
Type: Permanent
Salary: Competitive + Super

The Opportunity

We're looking for a hands-on software developer to build and integrate AI-powered services into our enterprise environment. This isn't a research or data science role — it's about shipping production AI solutions that work reliably within a Microsoft/.NET ecosystem.

You'll take established AI designs and turn them into real, running services — building APIs, integrating with existing systems, and ensuring everything operates securely at scale on Azure and Databricks.

What You'll Do

Build AI services and APIs — Develop inference and retrieval endpoints for LLMs, RAG pipelines, and ML models using Python, integrating them with our .NET platform

Integrate with enterprise systems — Connect AI capabilities to existing microservices, APIs, and legacy .NET applications

Operate in production — Deploy, monitor, and maintain AI workloads on Azure and Databricks with clear SLIs/SLOs for availability, latency, and cost

Develop secure pipelines — Build data pipelines for model training and retrieval with proper governance, privacy controls, and audit logging

Contribute to platform tooling — Work on CI/CD for models, MLflow experiment tracking, model registry, monitoring, and automated rollback

Write quality code — Deliver clean, well-tested code in both .NET and Python; participate in code reviews and maintain shared patterns

Apply security-first principles — Implement prompt protections, content filtering, access controls, and data minimisation across all AI touchpoints

Document and standardise — Maintain runbooks, ADRs, and contribute to reusable reference implementations

What We're Looking For

Must Have:

Strong development experience in .NET (C#) and Python

Minimum of 3+ years of professional experience in .NET (C#) development

Hands-on with Azure services — App Services, Functions, Container Apps, Key Vault, Azure DevOps

Experience with Azure Databricks — Delta Lake, Unity Catalog, MLflow, or similar data/ML platform work

Minimum of 2+ years of hands-on experience with Azure Databricks

Experience building and deploying APIs and microservices in production

Practical understanding of CI/CD pipelines and DevOps practices

Comfortable working with LLMs, RAG architectures, or AI/ML APIs (you don't need to train models — you need to integrate and operationalise them)

Security-conscious — familiar with identity management, secrets handling, and secure API design

Nice to Have:

Experience with Azure OpenAI or Azure AI Search

Background in enterprise environments with legacy system integration

Financial services or regulated industry experience

This Role is For You If...

You're a developer first — you ship working software, not Jupyter notebooks

You want to work with AI but aren't interested in pure research or model training

You've worked with Databricks and understand how to build reliable pipelines and workflows

You enjoy the challenge of integrating new tech into existing enterprise systems

You care about production reliability, security, and maintainability

You're comfortable in a Microsoft stack but can flex into Python for AI workloads

This Role is NOT For You If...

Your experience is primarily academic research or Kaggle competitions

You're looking for a pure data science or ML research position

You've never worked with .NET or Microsoft environments

You prefer greenfield projects over enterprise integration

About the Team

You'll join the AI Squad within the Data & AI team, reporting to the Group Manager Data & AI. The team is focused on delivering practical AI solutions that drive measurable business value — not experimentation for its own sake. You'll work closely with Product, Data, Security, and Operations to ship AI capabilities that actually get used.

Interested? Apply now or reach out to discuss.

Ad Text:
Enterprise Data Architect




Permanent, full-time position

Work on high-impact initiatives that drive V/Line operations

Play a key role in a collaborative, forward-thing team

 

V/Line’s purpose is to connect Victorians through safe, reliable, and accessible transport. We believe in giving all Victorians opportunities through travel and transport – connecting them to jobs, education, family and friends, services, tourism and trade.

V/Line is experiencing significant growth and we’re delivering more services, more trains, cheaper fares, and huge projects. With more than 3700 weekly train and coach services, an expansive freight network and unprecedented rail investment, millions of Victorians depend on us to deliver. You could be one of our 3100 committed team members who are up to the challenge.




About the role

As our new Enterprise Data Architect, you’ll play a key role in defining V/Line’s target data architecture and ensuring platforms, models and governance align with business needs. You’ll be the technical authority designing scalable, integrated data solutions that connect legacy systems with modern technologies to support enterprise-wide decision making.

Key Accountabilities include:

 Define and maintain enterprise data architecture principles, standards and patterns aligned to business strategy.

 Develop data models and integration patterns across structured and unstructured data.

 Design solutions that connect legacy systems with modern platforms to create a unified data ecosystem.

 Architect AI/ML platforms and infrastructure to enable advanced analytics.

 Build capability uplift roadmaps to transition from current to target-state architecture.

 Establish data architecture governance to ensure consistent delivery and compliance.

 Assess emerging technologies and recommend strategic adoption opportunities.

 Work closely with data engineers, analysts and governance teams to ensure successful delivery.

 Develop reusable reference architectures and design patterns.

 Ensure architectures support advanced analytics, ML and regulatory requirements.

 Translate business goals into clear architectural requirements through stakeholder engagement.

 

About you 

To be considered for this role, applicants must meet the following key selection criteria within their application, as this forms part of our merit-based recruitment process:

Must have 10+ years of experience successfully working in data architecture, engineering, or related roles.

Demonstrated experience designing architecture solutions for complex, siloed environments on cloud-native data platforms (AWS, Azure, Databricks, Snowflake).

Proven experience designing practical architectural solutions from complex business requirements, for both structured and unstructured data.

Strong understanding of data governance frameworks and regulatory requirements

Established experience creating architecture transition roadmaps, as well as designing data, AI and ML platforms and infrastructure.

Industry-recognised certification in AWS and/or Databricks (highly desirable).

Tertiary qualifications in IT, Business Management, or other related fields (highly desirable).

Experience working in similar industries e.g. Transport/Manufacturing/Logistics/Utilities (highly desirable)




Salary for this position is commensurate to the successful candidate’s aligned skills and experience to the position.




Why V/Line

In addition to free myki travel, we offer:

Community impact – Make a genuine difference. Work in a role that connects Victorians, every day.

Huge potential – We’re transforming, and you can too. Be a change maker, recognised for your contribution and creativity.

Dynamic environment – V/Line operates in a constantly changing space. Join a fast-paced and exciting organisation.

Collaborative team – You’ll be part of a broader supportive team. Surround yourself with talented, passionate peers.

Flexible working – We support flexible working. Work in a way that supports you to thrive in your role.




We are committed to ensuring a comfortable and accessible recruitment experience. If you need any adjustments or have specific accessibility requirements at any stage of the process, please contact our Talent team at TalentSupport@vline.com.au or 1800 800 007 for confidential support.




As an equal opportunity employer, V/Line is committed to creating a diverse, inclusive and respectful workplace and network that reflects the communities we serve. We accept and value the contributions of all our employees regardless of gender, ethnicity, sexual orientation, religion, age or disability. We are also proud to be endorsed by Work 180 as a great place for women to work, second year in a row.




V/Line are proud to be a part of the Department of Transport & Planning's Yani Bangal Transport and Planning Portfolio First Peoples Careers Strategy 2023-2028. We take this opportunity to welcome and encourage applications from First Peoples.  




At V/Line, safety is our priority. Successful applicants will undergo relevant pre-employment and medical checks to meet our safeworking standards.

We are seeking a skilled Python/Machine Learning Developer to join a market-leading client. This temporary role is remote and offers an exciting opportunity to contribute to innovative projects while leveraging your expertise in Python and machine learning.

Client Details

The employer is a global organisation within the software space, committed to delivering high-quality solutions through advanced technology. They focus on fostering a collaborative environment and prioritise innovation in their field

Description

Key responsibilities:

Develop and implement machine learning models to support project requirements.
Optimise Python code to ensure performance and scalability.
Collaborate with cross-functional teams to design and deliver technical solutions.
Analyse and interpret data to provide actionable insights.
Maintain and enhance existing machine learning systems and frameworks.
Document code and processes to ensure clarity and reproducibility.
Stay updated with the latest advancements in machine learning and Python development.
Assist in troubleshooting and resolving technical issues as they arise.

Profile

A successful Python/Machine Learning Developer should have:

Strong proficiency in Python programming and PyTorch
Strong machine learning experience
Experience in Linux/Containers/Docker
Capability to read, understand and implement from papers, i.e. Arxiv etc
Willingness to trial, implement and iterate rapidly on development solutions prior to refinement into production workflow.
Prior experience specifically in Computer Vision is a bonus
Familiarity with software development lifecycle and best practices.
Ability to work effectively in a team environment and communicate technical concepts clearly.
Problem-solving skills and a proactive approach to challenges.

Job Offer

Competitive daily rate
Fully remote role
Opportunity to work on cutting-edge projects
Collaborative and innovative work environment.

If you are a motivated Python/Machine Learning Developer ready to take on a rewarding challenge, we encourage you to apply now!

To apply online please click the 'Apply' button below. For a confidential discussion about this role please contact Uma Nayar.

Job details

The AI Engineer is primarily responsible for the design, development, testing and deployment of AI models and algorithms. The role works in collaboration with data scientists to define stakeholder requirements and deliver high quality, user centred solutions.

Key duties and responsibilities

Key duties and responsibilities for the role include:

Lead the design, engineering and deployment of data science and AI solutions in collaboration with data professionals, digital professionals and end users.
Architect, build and manage cloud infrastructure using Infrastructure as Code while ensuring appropriate security controls and scalability.
Drive strategic projects involving data ingestion and curation, exploratory data analysis, natural language processing, use of generative AI including agent based generative AI, predictive and prescriptive modelling, deployment of self service solutions and ad hoc data science products.
Prototype and develop engineering solutions at short notice for high priority data science and AI projects.
Coordinate and collaborate with other teams to build internal capability and establish or adopt standards and procedures across the development product life cycle.
Use customer centred approaches to design and prototype new technologies, tools and methods.
Work with IT service providers to specify requirements and support the establishment and upgrade of on premises and cloud infrastructure and tools.
Work closely with business users and IT service providers to select suitable technologies to deliver, manage and improve data science and AI solutions.
Key capabilities
Experience leading data, AI and cloud engineering work within the public sector or a complex multi stakeholder environment.
Experience establishing and maintaining rapport with clients and suppliers, including where there are no pre existing relationships.
Experience designing, implementing and managing relational databases such as Teradata, BigQuery or equivalent platforms.
Experience designing and implementing CI CD pipelines, monitoring systems, containerisation, orchestration and automation.
Experience working in Agile or other iterative delivery environments, including DevOps.
Experience designing and managing cloud infrastructure in Azure, AWS or Google Cloud.
Demonstrated ability to conduct independent research, address knowledge gaps and adopt emerging technologies to deliver innovative solutions.
Strong written and verbal communication skills, with the ability to translate technical concepts for non technical audiences.
Desirable experience
Experience implementing engineering solutions for generative AI including agent based solutions, prompt engineering and AI output evaluation.
Experience deploying open weight large language models, fine tuning them and integrating them with web applications via APIs.
Understanding of AI ethics, bias, risk and output evaluation frameworks.
Experience using Python based generative AI libraries such as Hugging Face Transformers, OpenVINO, Unsloth, llama cpp python, DSPy and PyTorch.
Experience working with structured and unstructured data, and strong data engineering capability for building reliable ETL pipelines.
* Experience using a business intelligence tool such as Power BI.
About the team

The Data Science Section is a central analytics unit within a large Australian Government portfolio, providing data science, analytics and engineering expertise across a broad range of business areas. The team contributes to organisational priorities through:

Delivering data driven insights to support strategic and operational decision making.
Identifying inefficiencies and optimisation opportunities to improve processes and resource allocation.
Applying predictive analytics to support risk identification and proactive planning.
Driving innovation through research and adoption of modern data science and AI techniques.

The team leads the integration of artificial intelligence and machine learning into business processes to support improvements in:

outcomes and accessibility for service recipients
system efficiency and sustainability
evidence base for policy development
efficiency in service delivery
About the organisation

The Data and Analytics Branch provides the evidence base to inform policies, programs and services through the safe and effective use of data. The broader division focuses on research, evaluation, innovation and analytics to support integrated, evidence based policy responses to current and future challenges.

Criteria

Each candidate must provide a one page pitch of up to 5000 characters addressing all criteria.

Essential criteria
Technical ability to design, develop, test and deploy AI engineering solutions.
Ability to work with stakeholders to identify requirements and develop appropriate solutions.
Ability to work collaboratively within a team and communicate effectively with non technical stakeholders.

Senior Data Engineer




Permanent, full-time position

Work on high-impact initiatives that drive V/Line operations

 Play a key role in a collaborative, forward-thing team

 

V/Line’s purpose is to connect Victorians through safe, reliable, and accessible transport. We believe in giving all Victorians opportunities through travel and transport – connecting them to jobs, education, family and friends, services, tourism and trade.

V/Line is experiencing significant growth and we’re delivering more services, more trains, cheaper fares, and huge projects. With more than 3700 weekly train and coach services, an expansive freight network and unprecedented rail investment, millions of Victorians depend on us to deliver. You could be one of our 3100 committed team members who are up to the challenge.




About the role

As our new Senior Data Engineer, you’ll play a pivotal role in establishing V/Line’s enterprise data foundation by designing, building and scaling high quality data pipelines and products on AWS and/or Databricks. You’ll lead complex data initiatives, apply best practice engineering, automation and governance, and ensure data is accurate, reliable and ready for analytics and AI, quality data pipelines and products on AWS and/or Databricks. Build robust, scalable ETL/ELT pipelines to ingest, transform and deliver data across business domains.

 Embed monitoring, validation and testing to ensure data is accurate, complete and timely.

 Drive automation through CI/CD and streamlined deployment processes.

 Work with analysts, data scientists and stakeholders to turn data requirements into practical solutions.

Must have 5+ years’ experience successfully working as a Senior Data Engineer (or equivalent), delivering scalable solutions on cloud-native data environments (preferably Databricks Lakehouse).

Proven track record designing, implementing and maintaining production-grade pipelines and working with large datasets.

Established experience with automation and DevOps practices, such as CI/CD pipelines, containerisation and infrastructure-as-code.

Demonstrated experience with data modelling, delivering within frameworks, modern data warehousing, data integrations and ETL best practices.

Industry-recognised certifications in Databricks and/or AWS (highly desirable).

About LEAP

LEAP is the leading provider of Legal Practice Management Solutions in the world and is part of ATI – one of the largest international LegalTech companies. For more than 30 years, our curiosity and commitment to continual improvement has kept us reimagining productivity tools for lawyers and their staff to support our guiding purpose, to ‘Help lawyers who help people’. The market-leading software we develop, and support is used by more than 70,000 lawyers and their staff in small and medium-sized law firms.

Working alongside our international team of passionate high achievers, you’ll join a fast-growing technology business where things seldom stay the same for long. With more than 800 smart, caring and ambitious ‘LEAPsters’ working together across Australia, Canada, the United States, the United Kingdom, the Republic of Ireland, Poland and New Zealand, you’ll find yourself in good company here.

Meet the Global Business Systems team

We’re a fast growing business built on a foundation of cutting edge technology and our Global Business Systems Teams are the sharp minds and steady hands keeping us running smoothly and making sure we’re always one step ahead. 

Whether you’re keeping user’s technology up to date, using analytics to solve complex business problems, or digitising processes to improve the ways we work, our technology specialists are the forward thinking experts keeping the engine of our continued success running – and the success of our clients too.  

If you’re a tech-savvy critical thinker with big ambitions and a passion to make an impact, you’ll discover not just a fulfilling career, but the opportunity to redefine the world of LegalTech. 

What you'll do

As our newest Analytics Engineer, you’ll be designing and scaling LEAP’s new enterprise data platform and semantic layer - the foundation for consistent metrics, AI enablement, and trusted insights that guide decisions across Executive, Product, Marketing, and Finance. This is a hands-on, engineering-focused role where you’ll partner closely with our BI Manager and Insight Analyst to ensure that metrics are standardised and data is accessible, trustworthy, and ready for both dashboards and advanced analytics. 

To make this happen, you will:

Build and maintain scalable, governed data models in dbt/Snowflake that power cross-functional reporting and advanced analytics. 
Develop and extend the universal semantic layer, ensuring metrics are consistent, reusable, and ready for both BI and AI applications. 
Structure high-quality, well-documented data assets that serve as the knowledge base for AI agents, predictive analytics, and self-service BI. 
Optimise and manage data pipelines (Fivetran/dbt) for reliability, performance and incremental refresh. 
Collaborate with the Data & Insights Analysts to translate the Metrics That Matter, a unified KPI framework across functions, into scalable, governed data models within the semantic layer. 
Ensure data quality and trust through testing, monitoring, and documentation.  

What you'll bring

Proficiency in SQL and modern data modelling (dbt preferred). 
Hands-on experience with Snowflake (or other cloud data warehouses). 
Familiarity with Fivetran (or similar ELT tools). 
Proven ability to design reusable, scalable data models that drive business outcomes. 
Experience integrating multiple data sources (Salesforce, Zuora, product usage, financial systems). 
Proactive, detail-oriented, and able to balance speed with governance. 
Experience with version control systems (Git preferred) and familiarity with CI/CD practices. 

Consider it a bonus if you have: 

Exposure to BI/visualisation tools (Tableau, Power BI, or similar). 
Experience with Python for data processing or automation. 
Interest in AI/ML integration (no need to be an expert yet). 

You are the type of person who

Has a collaborative, proactive mindset and you’re comfortable working in a fast-paced, evolving environment. 
Has strong communication skills, able to translate technical concepts into business outcomes. 
Is a self-starter attitude with a willingness to learn, experiment, and take ownership of tasks. 
Is a team player who understands that diverse opinions make a team and the benefit of achieving goals and decisions together. 
Is curious - you're not afraid to ask questions, explore and share your thoughts and ideas.  

LEAP is an inclusive, people-first company committed to breaking down institutional barriers that keep people from reaching their potential. If you meet some, but not all the requirements above, we encourage you to still submit your application.

Why join LEAP?

Your work matters. Helping lawyers help people sits at the heart of everything we do. We solve real world problems that improve and support local, everyday law firms. So they can do their best work for the people in the communities they serve.
Make an impact. You won’t be another ‘cog in the wheel’ here. We give full trust and autonomy for you to be heard, to work on big & complex projects – and to make a real difference.
Work with a group of authentic, passionate people who love what they do.
Well-funded and global. LEAP is the leading provider of Legal Practice Productivity Solutions across Australia, Canada, the United States, the United Kingdom, the Republic of Ireland and New Zealand. We're part of ATI – one of the largest international LegalTech companies.
Flexible and hybrid working. We'd like to find this person in Sydney, but we want you to work in a way that suits you and we're open to flexible arrangements that support you.
Grow your career with us. Our founder Christian Beck has been building legal tech businesses for over 30 years. There are opportunities galore to expand your career based on where your interests lie. We're not afraid to pivot based on market conditions - you will always have the opportunity to stay ahead of the curve and do your best work here.
Have fun with us. Celebrations. Socials. Sports teams. Access to sailing and yacht events.
We value your well-being - enjoy an additional paid wellbeing day every year, free gym membership, corporate dental plan and monthly massages in the office. We'll throw in a catered lunch and breakfast every week too. Oh and an on-site barista.
Access to LEAP Home - a program unique to LEAP to support you in buying your primary residence.

Role: AWS Cloud Engineer
Location: Melbourne
Daily rate: $800p.d. incl super
Telco experience would be preferred but not mandatory

About the client:
Our client is a major telecommunications and technology infrastructure provider, playing a key role in transforming the digital landscape of the nation.  
                           
About the role
Our client is seeking an AWS Cloud Engineer to design, build and operate enterprise‑scale AWS environments. This role will be heavily involved in cloud migration initiatives and ongoing platform operations, requiring strong security and networking expertise. The successful candidate should be comfortable working independently and contributing immediately.
  
Key Responsibilities
Design, build and operate AWS cloud infrastructure across multiple environments
Deliver and support large‑scale cloud migration projects (on‑prem to AWS and/or hybrid)
Implement and maintain AWS security best practices, governance controls and guardrails
Collaborate with application, security and network teams to deliver resilient, scalable solutions
Troubleshoot and resolve complex AWS infrastructure and networking issues
Drive operational improvements, automation and standardisation across cloud platforms
Provide technical guidance and hands‑on support across delivery teams
  
Required Experience & Skills
Minimum 5 years hands‑on AWS experience across design, build and operations
Strong experience with core AWS services (e.g., VPC, IAM, EC2, S3, RDS, Lambda, ECS/EKS)
Broad cloud security knowledge, including identity, network security, encryption and monitoring
Strong networking fundamentals (TCP/IP, DNS, routing, firewalls, VPNs, load balancing)
Proven experience delivering large cloud migration projects
Experience supporting live production environments
Self‑starter mindset with the ability to hit the ground running
  
Desirable
Infrastructure as Code experience (e.g., Terraform, CloudFormation, CDK)

Our client is seeking an Engineering Manager - AI Platform to lead a team of engineers building a platform that enables product teams to embed Generative AI into their solutions safely and effectively.
This role requires a strong software engineering background, combined with proven leadership skills to ensure delivery of secure, scalable, and ethical AI capabilities.

Key Responsibilities

Lead the design, build, and operation of cloud-native AI platform services (e.g. RAG, fine-tuning pipelines, evaluation tooling, AI agent frameworks).
Partner with Product, Data, Architecture, and Compliance to align AI adoption with enterprise guardrails.
Deliver reusable and composable AI components for use across multiple teams.
Champion responsible AI practices and operational excellence in production AI systems.
Hire, coach, and develop engineers, uplifting team capability and performance.
What We're Looking For

7+ years' software engineering experience, including at least 1 year in a leadership role.
Strong background in modern software development practices and cloud-native distributed systems (AWS preferred).
Experience with AI/ML pipelines and Generative AI (LLMs, RAG, embeddings, prompt engineering).
Familiarity with tools such as LangChain, Hugging Face, vector databases, or OpenAI APIs.
Proven ability to deliver complex software solutions while fostering a high-performance engineering culture.

Introduction

Kablamo is an Australian-based digital product development company, recognised for our diverse team and cutting-edge cloud and AI solutions. Founded in 2017, we have built a strong reputation and an extensive list of customers, including some of the best-known enterprise and government organisations in Australia and Canada. We design and build transformational software & AI solutions across Media & Entertainment, Fintech, Emergency Services and MedTech sectors, and we also proudly work with several high impact non-profit organisations.

We have established strategic partnerships with Google Cloud (GCP) and Amazon Web Services (AWS) and the company is experiencing strong demand for our AI-centric engineering, cloud and product development services. At the same time, we are actively re-defining and instituting more efficient software development lifecycles with a leading suite of GenAI tools. We’re seeking a Junior AI Engineer to work with our AI and Software Engineering teams to develop cutting edge AI & agentic solutions for our clients, and for Kablamo’s own suite of products.

The Role:

Kablamo has built a reputation as a strong software and cloud engineering company, with a proud track record of successfully scaling production software and solutions to mega scale. Over the last two years, our company has invested in building GenAI knowledge and capabilities, and we’ve established a dedicated AI technical discipline within our delivery teams. Our AI team

Kablamo’s AI team designs and builds Generative AI solutions, turning business problems into working software and solutions, powered by large language models and other AI/ML tools including computer vision, image generation, time-series forecasting, transcription etc. As a Junior AI Engineer, you'll work alongside senior engineers and technical leads to design, prototype, and deliver GenAI applications and solutions, from early proof-of-concepts through to production systems.

As part of the day to day working, you will work with LLMs via cloud platforms and APIs, build AI generated prototypes, create AI agents, integrate with data sources, and apply prompt engineering techniques to create solutions that are safe, secure, and cost-effective. You'll move quickly, building prototypes to demonstrate value, while learning to deliver production grade software to meet the standards and requirements of Kablamo’s enterprise and government customers.

We're looking for someone with solid software engineering fundamentals and a passion for GenAI. You don't need to know everything, but you do need the aptitude to learn fast and the initiative to solve problems. You'll receive guidance and mentorship from senior engineers, and over time you'll develop depth across the full range of GenAI engineering practices.

Responsibilities:

Contributes towards building GenAI applications by utilising LLM providers via cloud platforms (e.g. GCP, AWS) and best-in-class AI tools and solutions. Solutions can range from rapid prototypes and pilots through to contributions to client production systems.
Participates in GenAI driven software development projects, balancing speed of delivery with quality and security outcomes
Develops knowledge, skills and best practices with GenAI software development tools, such as Claude Code and Cursor
Applies prompt engineering and context management techniques to improve LLM output quality, delivering accurate, safe, and relevant outputs
Rapidly prototypes solutions to validate ideas and demonstrate capability to stakeholders
Contributes to production client work under the guidance of senior engineers
Writes and maintain basic evaluations/scripts to measure and improve GenAI application performance
Collaborates with other engineers to solve problems, share knowledge, and deliver work on time
Stays up-to-date with the fast-moving GenAI landscape and brings new ideas to the team
Documents work, including design decisions and lessons learned
Uses AI responsibly, safely and securely, in line with Kablamo’s and our clients’ policies
Contributes to Kablamo's internal knowledge base, templates, and best practices for GenAI engineering
Presents work alongside team members to internal stakeholders and clients.

Required skills and experience:

Bachelor's degree in Computer Science or Software Engineering (or equivalent practical experience)
Solid understanding of software engineering fundamentals: you can build a REST API, query a database, write tests, and use version control
Demonstrated experience with LLMs, prompt engineering, and/or building GenAI applications (professional, academic, or personal projects)
Passion and curiosity for GenAI, as evidenced by learning and practical applications
Experience working effectively in team environments, whether leading or contributing
Strong written and verbal communication skills—you can explain your work clearly and ask good questions
Commitment to responsible AI principles: ethics, safety, security

Desirable:

Has completed relevant internships whilst at University and/or has some software engineering work experience (we welcome graduate applicants)
Exposure to cloud platforms such as AWS or GCP
Knowledge of foundational AI frameworks, such as LangChain, LangGraph, CrewAI etc
Experience with AI-assisted coding tools (e.g. GitHub Copilot, Cursor, Claude)
Career Progression:
Mid-Level Engineer
Senior Level Engineer

Our Culture

We acknowledge a workplace that is diverse and inclusive, enables for greater innovation and producing benefits including improved performance, improved employee happiness and wellbeing, and superior outcomes for our customers. We attribute our success to all our unique and charismatic Kablamites. Through our fortnightly back-to-base, we enable our Kablamites to provide feedback, share ideas, challenge the status quo and technically challenge each other constructively.

Kablamo is a proud equal opportunity employer. We make our hiring decisions solely based on your skills and experience, as well as the perspectives and value you can bring to our team. Kablamo believes that diversity is vital to provide the best service to our clients and we are committed to fostering a varied and inclusive work environment. Every effort to accommodate candidates for accessibility will be made upon request. Information received related to accommodations will be addressed confidentially.

Kablamo would like to thank all candidates for their interest; however, only qualified applicants will be shortlisted.
